(212, 1, '2024-08-22 07:12:04', '2024-08-22 07:12:04', '[et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\"][et_pb_column _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" type=\"4_4\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" hover_enabled=\"0\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The ASEAN Centre for Biodiversity (ACB), through the project </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘌𝘧𝘧𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘪𝘷𝘦𝘭𝘺</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘔𝘢𝘯𝘢𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘨</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘕𝘦𝘵𝘸𝘰𝘳𝘬𝘴</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘰𝘧</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘔𝘢𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘗𝘳𝘰𝘵𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘦𝘥</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘈𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘴</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘪𝘯</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘓𝘢𝘳𝘨𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘔𝘢𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘌𝘤𝘰𝘴𝘺𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘮𝘴</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘪𝘯</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘵𝘩𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘈𝘚𝘌𝘈𝘕</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘙𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘰𝘯</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘈𝘚𝘌𝘈𝘕</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘌𝘕𝘔𝘈𝘗𝘚</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">),  has reaffirmed its dedication to preserving biodiversity while ensuring full and effective stakeholder engagement, aligning with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) Social and Environmental Standards (SES). This commitment is part of the broader ASEAN ENMAPS Project, supported by the Global Environment Facility (GEF) and UNDP, aimed at mainstreaming social and environmental sustainability across its programs and initiatives.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mr. Francis Falconi, ASEAN ENMAPS Regional Safeguards Consultant, led a comprehensive capacity-building orientation on the UNDP SES at the ACB Headquarters on 19 August 2024. This orientation served as a platform to deepen the understanding of the UNDP SES among the members of ASEAN ENMAPS Project Management Unit (PMU) and ACB’s Regional Project Coordinating Committee, ensuring that the project\'s activities adhere to the highest standards of social and environmental safeguards.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The orientation had three primary objectives:</span></p>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Introduction to UNDP SES.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The session provided the PMU with a thorough overview of the UNDP Social and Environmental Standards, emphasizing the importance of maximizing social and environmental benefits while mitigating potential risks.</span></p>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Safeguards compliance discussion.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Mr. Falconi presented the planned activities and relevant safeguards compliance requirements, including insights from the inception report, to align project activities with UNDP SES. This discussion also introduced a comprehensive consultation tool to facilitate effective stakeholder engagement.</span></p>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Harmonisation of activities.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The orientation aimed to synchronise the planned safeguards activities with the current implementation strategies and schedules of the PMU, ensuring seamless compliance with the necessary safeguards throughout the project lifecycle.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ACB’s commitment to upholding the UNDP SES underscores its dedication to conserving biodiversity in a manner that is inclusive, sustainable, and attuned to the needs of all stakeholders, particularly those directly impacted by the project.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'ACB strengthens commitment to conservation with inclusive stakeholder engagement', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'acb-strengthens-commitment-to-conservation-with-inclusive-stakeholder-engagement', '', '', '2024-08-28 02:09:46', '2024-08-28 02:09:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/enmaps/?p=212', 0, 'post', '', 0),
