(282, 1, '2024-08-29 01:41:53', '2024-08-29 01:41:53', '<!-- wp:divi/placeholder -->\n[et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\"][et_pb_column _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" type=\"4_4\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" theme_builder_area=\"post_content\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" header_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" hover_enabled=\"0\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The ASEAN Centre for Biodiversity (ACB), through the project </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘌𝘧𝘧𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘪𝘷𝘦𝘭𝘺</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘔𝘢𝘯𝘢𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘨</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘕𝘦𝘵𝘸𝘰𝘳𝘬𝘴</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘰𝘧</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘔𝘢𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘗𝘳𝘰𝘵𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘦𝘥</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘈𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘴</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘪𝘯</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘓𝘢𝘳𝘨𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘔𝘢𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘌𝘤𝘰𝘴𝘺𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘮𝘴</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘪𝘯</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘵𝘩𝘦</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘈𝘚𝘌𝘈𝘕</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘙𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘰𝘯</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘈𝘚𝘌𝘈𝘕</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">𝘌𝘕𝘔𝘈𝘗𝘚</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">) continues to support marine conservation efforts in the  ASEAN region as it actively participated in the 16th East Asian Seas (EAS) Partnership Council Meeting organised by the Partnerships in Environmental Management for the Seas of East Asia (PEMSEA) on 23–25 July 2024.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">During the meeting, Ms. Claudia B. Binondo, Director for Project Development of ACB’s Programmes Department, shared ACB’s strategic plans and activities under its coastal and marine biodiversity programme, including the proposed ACB’s session as co-convener of the EAS Congress 2024. These are all integrated in the Sustainable Development Strategy for the Seas of East Asia (SDS-SEA) as part of ACB’s contribution in its implementation..</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The SDS-SEA addresses common threats and outlines strategic action programmes aimed at mitigating the impacts of natural and manmade hazards on coastal and marine resources, as well as on the people, communities, and economies of the region. ASEAN ENMAPS is directly aligned with these goals, focusing on the protection and conservation of coastal and marine biodiversity by managing marine protected areas (MPAs) effectively. The project includes initiatives to monitor and reduce pollution within MPAs, enhancing the overall health of large marine ecosystems (LMEs).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ASEAN ENMAPS is implemented by the @UNDP through the funding of the Global Environment Facility, with ACB as the executing partner. It is implemented in 11 pilot sites within the LMEs of the three ASEAN Member States of Indonesia, the Philippines, and Thailand. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 16th EAS Partnership Council Meeting was convened by the PEMSEA Resource Facility and hosted by the Department of Environment and Natural Resources and the Provincial Environment and Natural Resources Office of Puerto Princesa City, Palawan. </span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]\n<!-- /wp:divi/placeholder -->', 'ACB unveils plans in support of SDS-SEA', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '266-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-08-29 01:41:53', '2024-08-29 01:41:53', '', 266, 'http://localhost/enmaps/?p=282', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
