/2024/08/bg1.jpg\" title_text=\"bg1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" hover_enabled=\"0\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" custom_margin=\"|-6%|||false|false\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"][/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" custom_padding=\"26px|20px|26px|20px|true|true\" hover_enabled=\"0\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"]<h2><b>Project Results-Based Framework</b></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Efforts to promote conservation through integrated coastal management, and marine spatial planning are progressing in the ASEAN region in terms of policy, planning, and implementation. However, effective multi-stakeholder collaboration remains a challenge, which hinders the realisation of these conservation investments.</span></p>\n<p><b><i>Barriers and causal pathways</i></b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The project baseline is marked by a lack of understanding of coastal and marine ecosystems, insufficient investment in MPA management, governance and financial issues, limited capacity for integrated approaches, and inadequate sharing of knowledge and best practices. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ASEAN ENMAPS’ Theory of Change highlights the causal pathways that the project will implement to move towards the GEF alternative scenario and achieve long-term outcomes: strengthened Blue Economy through integrated marine ecosystem management, achieving management goals, enhancing local community well-being through participatory approaches, reducing threats to coastal and marine ecosystems, and sharing knowledge for regional collaboration and replication across ASEAN Member States.  </span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" custom_padding=\"19px|||||\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<h2><b>Project Information</b></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ASEAN ENMAPS is designed to address the threats facing the coastal and marine environment in the ASEAN region by facilitating transformative changes in the management of MPAs and other coastal and marine resources in ASEAN LMEs. The project strategy has a strong upscaling focus as it engages with ASEAN working groups and LME cooperative governance, while leveraging complementary investments across the region.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Participating Countries</b></td>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Republic of Indonesia</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Republic of the Philippines</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kingdom of Thailand</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Funding Agency </b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">GEF </span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Implementing Agency </b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UNDP Bangkok Regional Hub </span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Executing Agency </b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ACB </span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>National Executing Partners</b></td>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ministry of Environment and Forestry (Indonesia)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Department of Environment and Natural Resources (Philippines)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Office of Natural Resources and Environmental Policy and Planning (Thailand)</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Project Duration</b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">March 2024 to March 2029</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Total Budget</b></td>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">GEF Investment: USD 12,548,861</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Co-financing: USD 57,907,646</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '48-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-08-29 05:05:36', '2024-08-29 05:05:36', '', 48, 'http://localhost/enmaps/?p=320', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
