(340, 1, '2024-08-29 05:40:39', '2024-08-29 05:40:39', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use the block-moving tools to move the&nbsp;<strong>Post Template</strong>&nbsp;block. The six dots icon allows you to freely reposition the block anywhere within the editor by dragging and dropping it. You can also use the arrows icon to move the block up or down the editor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Change alignment</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/aJuuJl0HhzNAQ-ZUpyPSxj-vyE-qeNOCuiEBTdWXDeVInbNRgJMcMwTt8N-pxz51D8TNvndZUqWyAP9K2e3njX7dHqiyu07lCDGfeMY4OGN08YIRqPy4ZoLcjfx3aH0hcJEBi65TPPZRVDoTsBquzztYlLFwca71F3USXlwrjuddYRvh0vHSXUSYmGVdQw\" alt=\"Change alignment in the Post Template block\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use the change alignment tool to reposition the&nbsp;<strong>Post Template</strong>&nbsp;block inside the Query Loop block. The following is a list of the block alignment options:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>None</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Wide width</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Full width</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Align left</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Align center</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Align right</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the parent Query Loop block’s Layout settings –&nbsp;<strong>inner blocks use content width</strong>&nbsp;option is enabled, the&nbsp;<strong>Post Template</strong>&nbsp;block will inherit the layout settings from the parent Query Loop block.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/rgzEKxvx-2AJHWCTa